      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 debug read-peripheral NVIC",
        "description": "Read NVIC peripheral state to check interrupt enables"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 debug read-peripheral USART2",
        "description": "Read USART2 peripheral state to check local interrupt enable bits"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "I'll check both the NVIC (for the USART2 IRQ line enable) and the USART2 peripheral (for its own interrupt-enable bits) in parallel.\n**No \u2014 NVIC interrupts for USART2 are not enabled, at either level.**\n\nHere's the full picture from both reads:\n\n---\n\n### 1. NVIC \u2014 IRQ line (IRQ #38)\n\nOn STM32L476, USART2 maps to **IRQ #38**, which lives in `NVIC_ISER1` (covers IRQs 32\u201363) at **bit 6**.\n\n| Register | raw_value | USART2 bit (bit 6) |\n|---|---|---|\n| `NVIC_ISER1` | `0x00000000` | **0 \u2014 not enabled** |\n\nAll eight `NVIC_ISERx` registers read back `0`, so no peripheral interrupt line is enabled in the NVIC at all.\n\n---\n\n### 2. USART2 CR1/CR3 \u2014 peripheral-side interrupt enables\n\nEvery interrupt-enable bit in USART2 is also cleared:\n\n| Register | Field | Value | Meaning |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| CR1 | `RXNEIE` | 0 | RX-not-empty IRQ disabled |\n| CR1 | `TXEIE` | 0 | TX-empty IRQ disabled |\n| CR1 | `TCIE` | 0 | Transmit-complete IRQ disabled |\n| CR1 | `IDLEIE` | 0 | Idle-line IRQ disabled |\n| CR1 | `PEIE` | 0 | Parity-error IRQ disabled |\n| CR3 | `EIE` | 0 | Error IRQ disabled |\n| CR3 | `CTSIE` | 0 | CTS IRQ disabled |\n| CR3 | `WUFIE` | 0 | Wake-up IRQ disabled |\n\nAlso: `CR1.UE = 0` \u2014 USART2 isn't even enabled yet (ISR shows `TXE=1, TC=1`, which are just the idle/reset defaults).\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** Interrupts are disabled at both gates \u2014 the NVIC IRQ line (ISER1 bit 6 = 0) and every USART2 CR1/CR3 `*IE` bit. To get USART2 interrupts firing you'll need to set at least one `*IE` bit (e.g. `RXNEIE`) *and* set bit 6 of `NVIC_ISER1` (or call `HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ(USART2_IRQn)`)."
}